Rating: 3
Made this last night, and really enjoyed it. I love parsnips (and yes, they were a bit stinky while roasting), but didn't have quite enough, so threw in a celery root to top up the veggies. Was trying to decide between this recipe and the Celery and Parsnip soup with dill matzo balls on this website, and opted for this because I had no celery, but liked the idea of the two flavours together. The two roots worked very well, and flavours were mellow. Bacon and sour cream added to it (of course!). Will certainly make again.

